{"parse":{"title":"Hans Alfred Nieper","pageid":22381410,"revid":833250660,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox biography vcard\" style=\"width:22em\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold\"><span class=\"fn\">Hans Alfred Nieper</span></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/File:Nieper-1600.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Nieper-1600.jpg\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/af/Nieper-1600.jpg/220px-Nieper-1600.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"302\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/af/Nieper-1600.jpg/330px-Nieper-1600.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/a/af/Nieper-1600.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"350\" data-file-height=\"480\" /></a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Born</th><td>\n23 May 1928<br /><span class=\"birthplace\"><a href=\"/wiki/Germany\" title=\"Germany\">Germany</a></span></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Died</th><td>\n21 October 1998 (aged 70)</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Nationality</th><td class=\"category\">\nGerman</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Citizenship</th><td class=\"category\">\nGerman</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Education</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Albert_Ludwigs_University_of_Freiburg\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Albert Ludwigs University of Freiburg\">Albert Ludwigs University of Freiburg</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Hamburg\" title=\"University of Hamburg\">University of Hamburg</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Occupation</th><td class=\"role\">\nPhysician</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Known&#160;for</th><td>\nAlternative medicine</td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<b>Medical career</b></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Profession</th><td class=\"role\">\nDoctor</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Field</th><td class=\"category\">\nAlternative medicine</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Institutions</th><td class=\"org\">\nSilbersee Hospital</td></tr><tr style=\"display:none\"><td colspan=\"2\">\n</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Hans Alfred Herbert Eugen Nieper</b> (23 May 1928 \u2013 21 October 1998) was a controversial German <a href=\"/wiki/Alternative_medicine\" title=\"Alternative medicine\">alternative medicine</a> practitioner who devised \"Nieper Therapy\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-Lerner_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Lerner-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-qw_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-qw-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> He is best known for his claims to be able to treat <a href=\"/wiki/Cancer\" title=\"Cancer\">cancer</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Multiple_sclerosis\" title=\"Multiple sclerosis\">multiple sclerosis</a>, and other serious diseases. In 1986 an FDA release discredited his therapy as ineffective and unsafe. There is, however, no record official record of this FDA release. <sup id=\"cite_ref-qw_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-qw-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Family_Background_and_Early_life\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Family Background and Early life</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Career_and_Discoveries\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Career and Discoveries</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#See_also\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">See also</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Family_Background_and_Early_life\">Family Background and Early life</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Hans_Alfred_Nieper&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Family Background and Early life\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Hans Nieper was born in Hanover, Germany on May 23, 1928. His parents - who were both physicians - were Ferdinand Nieper (b. 1887) and Margarete Krauss (b.1898).<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup><sup class=\"noprint Inline-Template\" style=\"white-space:nowrap;\">&#91;<i><a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Identifying_reliable_sources\" title=\"Wikipedia:Identifying reliable sources\"><span title=\"The material near this tag may rely on an unreliable source. (October 2017)\">unreliable source?</span></a></i>&#93;</sup> They were married in 1925. Shortly after getting married, Hans' parents began working at the Wahrendorff Psychiatric Hospital (now known as <a href=\"https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Klinikum_Wahrendorff\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"de:Klinikum Wahrendorff\">de:Klinikum Wahrendorff</a>) at Sehnde-Ilten, near Hanover.<sup id=\"cite_ref-life_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-life-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup><sup class=\"noprint Inline-Template noprint Template-Fact\" style=\"white-space:nowrap;\">&#91;<i><a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:No_original_research#Primary,_secondary_and_tertiary_sources\" title=\"Wikipedia:No original research\"><span title=\"This claim needs references to reliable secondary sources. (October 2017)\">non-primary source needed</span></a></i>&#93;</sup>\n</p><p>Hans' fascination with science and medicine came long before he was a physician. Coming from a family with an extensive background in medicine, Hans  eventually followed in the family footsteps and became a physician himself.<sup id=\"cite_ref-life_4-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-life-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup><sup class=\"noprint Inline-Template noprint Template-Fact\" style=\"white-space:nowrap;\">&#91;<i><a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:No_original_research#Primary,_secondary_and_tertiary_sources\" title=\"Wikipedia:No original research\"><span title=\"This claim needs references to reliable secondary sources. (October 2017)\">non-primary source needed</span></a></i>&#93;</sup>\n</p><p>Hans' father Ferdinand Nieper was a son of Herbert Nieper (1848-1939),<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup><sup class=\"noprint Inline-Template\" style=\"white-space:nowrap;\">&#91;<i><a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Identifying_reliable_sources\" title=\"Wikipedia:Identifying reliable sources\"><span title=\"The material near this tag may rely on an unreliable source. (October 2017)\">unreliable source?</span></a></i>&#93;</sup> who was the Chief Surgeon at the hospital in <a href=\"/wiki/Goslar\" title=\"Goslar\">Goslar</a>, which was renamed the Dr.-Herbert-Nieper-Krankenhaus<sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> in his honor. In 1879 Hans' grandfather Dr. Herbert Nieper married Karla Marie Johanne Elisabeth Wahrendorff (b. August 21, 1859), who was a daughter of Ferdinand Wahrendorff (1826-1898),<sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup><sup class=\"noprint Inline-Template\" style=\"white-space:nowrap;\">&#91;<i><a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Identifying_reliable_sources\" title=\"Wikipedia:Identifying reliable sources\"><span title=\"The material near this tag may rely on an unreliable source. (October 2017)\">unreliable source?</span></a></i>&#93;</sup> founder of the Wahrendorff Psychiatric Hospital.\n</p><p>As a child and adolescent, Hans spent most of his time at the Wahrendorff Psychiatric Hospital. His parents granted him complete intellectual freedom. As he matured, Hans' parents encouraged him to participate in stimulating conversations about the nature of the mind, the relationship between biology and mentality, and the validity of orthodox medicine, and to ask questions and raise points on his own. These experiences in Hans' early years taught him to think analytically, to question orthodox assumptions, and to explore ideas and thoughts without fear of censure or ridicule.<sup id=\"cite_ref-life_4-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-life-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup><sup class=\"noprint Inline-Template noprint Template-Fact\" style=\"white-space:nowrap;\">&#91;<i><a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:No_original_research#Primary,_secondary_and_tertiary_sources\" title=\"Wikipedia:No original research\"><span title=\"This claim needs references to reliable secondary sources. (October 2017)\">non-primary source needed</span></a></i>&#93;</sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Career_and_Discoveries\">Career and Discoveries</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Hans_Alfred_Nieper&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Career and Discoveries\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Hans Nieper was educated at the <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Mainz\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"University of Mainz\">Johann Gutenberg University</a> and the <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Freiberg\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"University of Freiberg\">University of Freiberg</a> before earning his <a href=\"/wiki/Doctor_of_Medicine\" title=\"Doctor of Medicine\">medical degree</a> at the <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Hamburg\" title=\"University of Hamburg\">University of Hamburg</a>. During his career, he served as Director of the Department of Medicine at the Paracelsus-Klinik am Silbersee (Paracelsus Silbersee Hospital) in <a href=\"/wiki/Hanover\" title=\"Hanover\">Hanover</a>-<a href=\"/wiki/Langenhagen\" title=\"Langenhagen\">Langenhagen</a>, and as Director of the German Society for Medical Tumour Treatment.<sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Nieper was among the first researchers to work with <a href=\"/wiki/Lithium_orotate\" title=\"Lithium orotate\">lithium orotate</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Lerner_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Lerner-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Nieper and biochemist Dr. Franz Josef K\u00f6hler (1909-1984)<sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-10\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup> patented Calcium AEP (<a href=\"/wiki/Calcium_2-aminoethylphosphate\" title=\"Calcium 2-aminoethylphosphate\">Calcium 2-aminoethylphosphate</a>), which they believed could be helpful in combating such diseases as <a href=\"/wiki/Juvenile_diabetes\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Juvenile diabetes\">juvenile diabetes</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Gastritis\" title=\"Gastritis\">gastritis</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Peptic_ulcer\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Peptic ulcer\">ulcer</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Thyroiditis\" title=\"Thyroiditis\">thyroiditis</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Myocarditis\" title=\"Myocarditis\">Myocarditis</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Hodgkin%27s_Disease\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Hodgkin&#39;s Disease\">Hodgkin's Disease</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-11\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup> However, there is no evidence from reputable <a href=\"/wiki/Clinical_trials\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Clinical trials\">clinical trials</a> for the success of the \"Nieper Regime\" for treating multiple sclerosis utilizing Calcium AEP.<sup id=\"cite_ref-12\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup> The \"Nieper Therapy\" approach to cancer also uses Calcium AEP, along with <a href=\"/wiki/Selenium\" title=\"Selenium\">selenium</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-13\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-13\">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup> It is based in part upon Nieper's belief that cancer is rarer among <a href=\"/wiki/Shark\" title=\"Shark\">sharks</a> than other <a href=\"/wiki/Fish\" title=\"Fish\">fish</a>, and upon his theory that the lower blood-<a href=\"/wiki/Sodium\" title=\"Sodium\">sodium</a> level of sharks may be the reason. \"Nieper Therapy\" places among its primary goals the reduction of that sodium in cancer patients.<sup id=\"cite_ref-14\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-14\">&#91;14&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-15\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-15\">&#91;15&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Hans_Alfred_Nieper&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/List_of_unproven_and_disproven_cancer_treatments\" title=\"List of unproven and disproven cancer treatments\">List of unproven and disproven cancer treatments</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Quackery\" title=\"Quackery\">Quackery</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Hans_Alfred_Nieper&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist columns references-column-width\" style=\"-moz-column-width: 30em; -webkit-column-width: 30em; column-width: 30em; list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Lerner-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-Lerner_1-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Lerner_1-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Lerner, Michael (1996). <i>Choices in Healing: Integrating the Best of Conventional and Complementary Approaches to Cancer</i>. MIT Press. p.&#160;600. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-262-62104-5\" title=\"Special:BookSources/0-262-62104-5\">0-262-62104-5</a>. <q>Hans Nieper is a controversial German alternative cancer therapist who receives mixed reviews from American cancer patients who visit him.</q></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Choices+in+Healing%3A+Integrating+the+Best+of+Conventional+and+Complementary+Approaches+to+Cancer&amp;rft.pages=600&amp;rft.pub=MIT+Press&amp;rft.date=1996&amp;rft.isbn=0-262-62104-5&amp;rft.aulast=Lerner&amp;rft.aufirst=Michael&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHans+Alfred+Nieper\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-qw-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-qw_2-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-qw_2-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\">FDA Press Office (15 August 1986). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.quackwatch.org/01QuackeryRelatedTopics/nieper.html\">\"Alert Issued on Nieper Therapies\"</a>. Quackwatch.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Alert+Issued+on+Nieper+Therapies&amp;rft.pub=Quackwatch&amp;rft.date=1986-08-15&amp;rft.au=FDA+Press+Office&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.quackwatch.org%2F01QuackeryRelatedTopics%2Fnieper.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHans+Alfred+Nieper\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Her full name was Margarete Friederike Anne Viktoria Krauss.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-life-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-life_4-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-life_4-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-life_4-2\"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Nieper, H.; Alexander, A. (1999). <i>The Curious Man: The Life and Works of Dr. Hans Nieper</i>. Garden City Park, N.Y.: Avery.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Curious+Man%3A+The+Life+and+Works+of+Dr.+Hans+Nieper&amp;rft.place=Garden+City+Park%2C+N.Y.&amp;rft.pub=Avery&amp;rft.date=1999&amp;rft.aulast=Nieper&amp;rft.aufirst=H.&amp;rft.au=Alexander%2C+A.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHans+Alfred+Nieper\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">His full name was Herbert Otto Wilhelm August Nieper (1848 - May 23, 1939).</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-6\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">The Dr.-Herbert-Nieper-Krankenhaus is now a privately-owned hospital of the Asklepios Harzkliniken group, serving the greater Harz region.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-7\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">His full name was August Ernst Ferdinand Leonhard Theodor Wahrendorff (February 20, 1826 - March 21, 1898). On October 5, 1854 he married Friederike Amalie Juliane Charlotte Sophie von Jeinsen (1826 - May 13, 1898).</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-8\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-8\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Emeka, Mauris L. (2002). <i>Fear Cancer No More: Preventive and Healing Information Everyone Should Know</i>. Health Research Books. p.&#160;94. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-9640125-6-1\" title=\"Special:BookSources/0-9640125-6-1\">0-9640125-6-1</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Fear+Cancer+No+More%3A+Preventive+and+Healing+Information+Everyone+Should+Know&amp;rft.pages=94&amp;rft.pub=Health+Research+Books&amp;rft.date=2002&amp;rft.isbn=0-9640125-6-1&amp;rft.aulast=Emeka&amp;rft.aufirst=Mauris+L.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHans+Alfred+Nieper\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-9\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-9\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Dr. Franz Josef K\u00f6hler (October 2, 1909 - September 22, 1984) was a German biochemist and inventor. He was the originator of \"aspartate therapy\" and of various organ-protecting chemical solutions, which he promoted and sold through his company Dr. Franz K\u00f6hler Chemie GmbH. He founded this company in 1959 in Alsbach-Hahnlein, DE, Germany.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-10\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-10\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.koehler-chemie.de/deutsch/wir/franz-j.koehler-preis/franz-j.-koehler-preis-franz-josef-koehler.html\">Biography of Dr. Franz Josef K\u00f6hler (1909-1984), and History of Dr. Franz K\u00f6hler Chemie GmbH</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-11\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-11\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Zerden, Sheldon; Richard Passwater; Abram Hoffer (2004). <i>The Best of Health: The 100 Best Health Books</i>. Warren H. Green Inc. p.&#160;179. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-87527-537-0\" title=\"Special:BookSources/0-87527-537-0\">0-87527-537-0</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Best+of+Health%3A+The+100+Best+Health+Books&amp;rft.pages=179&amp;rft.pub=Warren+H.+Green+Inc.&amp;rft.date=2004&amp;rft.isbn=0-87527-537-0&amp;rft.aulast=Zerden&amp;rft.aufirst=Sheldon&amp;rft.au=Richard+Passwater&amp;rft.au=Abram+Hoffer&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHans+Alfred+Nieper\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-12\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-12\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Bowling, Allen C. (2006). <i>Complementary and Alternative Medicine and Multiple Sclerosis</i> (2nd ed.). Demos Medical Publishing, LLC. p.&#160;231. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/1-932603-54-9\" title=\"Special:BookSources/1-932603-54-9\">1-932603-54-9</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Complementary+and+Alternative+Medicine+and+Multiple+Sclerosis&amp;rft.pages=231&amp;rft.edition=2nd&amp;rft.pub=Demos+Medical+Publishing%2C+LLC&amp;rft.date=2006&amp;rft.isbn=1-932603-54-9&amp;rft.aulast=Bowling&amp;rft.aufirst=Allen+C.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHans+Alfred+Nieper\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span>